## Next steps

Import and use in your command handlers:

```ts
import { emit, note, reportError, detectMode } from './agent/json-mode';

program
  .option('--json', 'emit JSON for agents')
  .command('list')
  .action(async (opts) => {
    note('Fetching items...', opts);
    const items = await fetchItems();
    emit(items, opts, (data) => {
      for (const item of data) console.log(`- ${item.name}`);
    });
  });
```

In JSON mode (`--json` or piped stdout): NDJSON to stdout, nothing to stderr.
In human mode (TTY): formatted output to stdout, notes to stderr.

Pairs with `next-steps` block for agent-first CLIs.
